parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the ignition switch can cause the vehicle to stall or shut off while driving, leading to accidents or leaving the driver stranded.
symptoms: The vehicle stalls or shuts off while driving
the engine dies
the car won't start
the key gets stuck in the ignition
or the dash lights flicker.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the electrical system can cause the vehicle to stall or shut off while driving, leading to accidents or leaving the driver stranded.
symptoms: The vehicle stalls or shuts off while driving
the engine dies
the car won't start
the dash lights flicker
or the power surges.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the transmission can cause the vehicle to stall or shut off while driving, leading to accidents or leaving the driver stranded.
symptoms: The vehicle stalls or shuts off while driving
the engine dies
the car won't start
or the transmission solenoid fails.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the alarm system can cause inconvenience and additional costs to the vehicle owner.
symptoms: The alarm system is not operating after the recall repair
or the dealership charges to reconnect the alarm system.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the airbag to deploy in the event of a crash can lead to serious injuries or fatalities, compromising the safety of the vehicle occupants.
symptoms: Airbag failure to deploy
lack of warning lights or signals prior to the crash
and injuries or fatalities resulting from the crash.

parsedComplaintsResult.issueCategory: Unavailable Recall Parts for Takata Airbag Recall
parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The unavailability of recall parts for the Takata airbag recall can leave vehicle owners without a functioning airbag system, putting them at risk of injury or death in the event of a crash.
symptoms: Notification of recall
but parts are not available
manufacturer exceeds a reasonable amount of time for recall repair
and vehicle owners are left without a functioning airbag system.

parsedComplaintsResult.issueCategory: Airbag System Disablement after Battery Replacement
parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The disablement of the airbag system after a battery replacement can leave the vehicle occupants without protection in the event of a crash, increasing the risk of injury or death.
symptoms: Airbag system disablement after battery replacement
SRS light remains on
and the need to pay for a service center to enable the system.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: Unintended airbag deployment can cause accidents, injuries, or fatalities, and can also lead to a loss of control of the vehicle.
symptoms: Unintended airbag deployment
loss of control of the vehicle
and injuries or fatalities resulting from the deployment.

parsedComplaintsResult.issueCategory: Transmission Failure - Slipping and Loss of Gear
parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The transmission failure can cause the vehicle to lose power, slip out of gear, and potentially lead to accidents, especially when driving at high speeds.
symptoms: The transmission slips violently out of gear
the vehicle jerks forward when accelerating
the transmission does not shift correctly
the vehicle is unable to move
the transmission goes into neutral by itself
the RPMs surge to high levels.

parsedComplaintsResult.issueCategory: Transmission Failure - Intermittent Loss of Power
parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The intermittent loss of power can cause the vehicle to stall or lose power, leading to accidents or leaving the driver stranded.
symptoms: The vehicle cuts off in the middle of traffic
the vehicle is unable to crank
the transmission does not engage
the vehicle jerks forward when accelerating.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the clutch pedal can cause the vehicle to lose power, making it difficult or impossible to shift gears, which can lead to accidents or leave the driver stranded.
symptoms: The clutch pedal feels soft or spongy
the clutch pedal sticks to the floor
the clutch pedal does not return to its normal position.
